# No `Co-authored-by: Cursor` in Any Commit

**NEVER** allow `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` to appear in any commit
pushed to a remote. Cursor injects this trailer into every commit message at the agent
level — the `grep -v` amend approach does **not** work because the agent re-injects the
trailer during the amend itself.

## The Fix — `commit-msg` Git Hook

Install this hook once per repo. It strips the trailer before git finalises the commit:

```bash
cat > .git/hooks/commit-msg << 'EOF'
#!/bin/sh
grep -v '^Co-authored-by: Cursor' "$1" | grep -v '^Co-authored-by:.*cursoragent' > "$1.tmp" && mv "$1.tmp" "$1"
exit 0
EOF
chmod +x .git/hooks/commit-msg
```

### Verify the hook is in place before your first commit in any repo

```bash
ls -la .git/hooks/commit-msg
```

If missing, install it (above) **before** committing anything.

---

## Fixing Already-Pushed Commits

If the trailer slipped through on commits already on the remote:

```bash
# Rewrite all commit messages locally
FILTER_BRANCH_SQUELCH_WARNING=1 git filter-branch --msg-filter \
  'grep -v "^Co-authored-by: Cursor"' -- --all

# Force-push to replace remote history
# (safe on personal repos; warn the team on shared repos first)
git push --force origin <branch>
```

---

## Why the Amend Approach Fails

```
# ❌ This does NOT work — Cursor re-injects the trailer during the amend
git commit -m "msg"
git commit --amend -m "$(git log -1 --pretty=%B | grep -v 'Co-authored-by')"
```

The `commit-msg` hook runs inside git's own commit process, **after** Cursor injects the
trailer but **before** the commit is finalised — that is why it works where amend cannot.
